{"type":"message","id":"3fa7ad8f","parentId":"900ef1f3","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:06:42.385Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 20:06 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Validate OC-System-Evolver for Real Operational Scenarios\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `OC-System-Evolver` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because:\n- Only proven for scheduled improvements (cron job `oc-system-evolver-mwf`)\n- Not validated for real operational scenarios\n- Unknown if can generate improvement proposals from real system analysis\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nProve `OC-System-Evolver` functionality for REAL operational scenarios, not just scheduled improvements.\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES (ABSOLUTE)\n- NO simulated improvement proposals\n- NO fake system analysis\n- NO placeholder evidence\n- REAL system analysis → REAL improvement proposals → REAL actionable changes\n- Evidence must be operational, not narrative\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Test Real System Analysis\n- Analyze current OpenClaw system state for real\n- Identify actual gaps, issues, or improvement opportunities\n- Use real system metrics, logs, artifacts\n\n### 2. Generate Real Improvement Proposals\n- Based on real system analysis\n- Specific, actionable proposals\n- With operational impact assessment\n- Prioritized by real value\n\n### 3. Prove Operational Value\n- Show how proposals would improve system\n- Demonstrate actionable nature\n- Provide implementation guidance\n- Show integration with existing processes\n\n### 4. Validate End-to-End\n- System analysis → improvement proposals → actionable changes\n- Real evidence at each step\n- No simulation or placeholder content\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS\n\n### Scenario 1: Real System Health Analysis\n- Analyze current system health metrics\n- Identify real improvement opportunities\n- Generate specific proposals\n\n### Scenario 2: Skill Performance Analysis\n- Analyze skill performance based on real usage\n- Identify optimization opportunities\n- Generate improvement proposals\n\n### Scenario 3: Integration Gap Analysis\n- Analyze integration points between skills\n- Identify gaps or inefficiencies\n- Generate integration improvement proposals\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n### Must Provide:\n1. **Real system analysis output** - Not simulated\n2. **Real improvement proposals** - Specific, actionable\n3. **Operational impact assessment** - Real value demonstrated\n4. **Implementation guidance** - How to implement proposals\n5. **Integration evidence** - How proposals integrate with system\n\n### Must NOT Provide:\n- Simulated analysis\n- Placeholder proposals\n- Generic recommendations\n- Documentation-only \"improvements\"\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`OC-System-Evolver` becomes FUNCTIONAL when:\n1. Real system analysis produces real insights\n2. Real improvement proposals generated\n3. Proposals are actionable with operational impact\n4. Evidence shows end-to-end real functionality\n\n## FAILURE CRITERIA\nRemains PARTIAL if:\n1. Only simulated analysis\n2. Placeholder proposals\n3. No real operational evidence\n4. Cannot prove real functionality\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 20 minutes\n- Report: Concise with operational evidence\n\nProceed to validate REAL operational capability."}],"timestamp":1773104802383}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c2f2b31","parentId":"3fa7ad8f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:06:49.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll validate the OC-System-Evolver skill for real operational scenarios. Let me start by examining the skill itself to understand its capabilities."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fVhQvKUmhmVrGsVOsxObdx4e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":11808,"output":91,"cacheRead":2304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14203,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773104802384}}
{"type":"message","id":"4225c88a","parentId":"0c2f2b31","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:06:49.688Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_fVhQvKUmhmVrGsVOsxObdx4e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: oc-system-evolver\ndescription: An autonomic system evolution and self-healing skill that enables OpenClaw to safely improve, repair, and maintain its own ecosystem through a hardened evolution layer with strict safety guarantees, controlled change mechanisms, and rollback protection.\ncategory: system\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"oc-respawner\"]\noptional_requires: [\"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# OC-System-Evolver Skill\n\n## Overview\n**OC-System-Evolver** is an autonomic system evolution and self-healing skill that enables OpenClaw to safely improve, repair, and maintain its own ecosystem. It implements a hardened evolution layer with strict safety guarantees, controlled change mechanisms, and rollback protection.\n\n## Core Philosophy\n- **Never blindly modify the environment**\n- **All changes go through detection → classification → simulation → snapshot → validation → rollback**\n- **Safety first, evolution second**\n\n## Autonomic Loop\nThe skill implements the following autonomic computing cycle:\n1. **Observe** - Scan system using OC-Respawner as source of truth\n2. **Analyze** - Detect issues from error-learning-loop and watchdog\n3. **Plan** - Create structured improvement proposals\n4. **Simulate** - Predict impact before execution\n5. **Snapshot** - Create minimal targeted backups\n6. **Execute** - Apply minimal required changes\n7. **Validate** - Run comprehensive test suite\n8. **Commit/Rollback** - Decide based on validation results\n9. **Learn** - Feed outcomes to error-learning-loop\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### OC-Intent-Governor\n- Validates clarity of improvement instructions before execution\n- Ensures evolution instructions are unambiguous\n\n### OC-Respawner\n- Source of truth for system architecture\n- Provides registry for system validation\n\n### Error-Learning-Loop\n- Supplies incident intelligence for analysis\n- Stores lessons learned from evolution outcomes\n\n### Workspace-Janitor\n- Cleans snapshots, logs, and temporary artifacts\n- Manages snapshot retention (48-hour policy)\n\n### Agent-Watchdog\n- Monitors long-running evolution tasks\n- Detects stalls and initiates recovery\n\n## File Structure\n```\nskills/OC-System-Evolver/\n├── SKILL.md (this file)\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── system_observer.py\n│   ├── improvement_engine.py\n│   ├── change_classifier.py\n│   ├── change_simulator.py\n│   ├── snapshot_manager.py\n│   ├── test_runner.py\n│   └── rollback_manager.py\n├── references/\n│   ├── AUTONOMIC_LOOP.md\n│   ├── CHANGE_CLASSIFICATION.md\n│   └── TEST_MANIFEST.md\n└── examples/\n    ├── example_change_plan.md\n    ├── example_snapshot.md\n    └── example_test_results.md\n```\n\n## Runtime Directories\n```\nworkspace/system_evolution/\n├── EVOLUTION_REGISTRY.md\n├── SYSTEM_HEALTH_REPORT.md\n├── IMPROVEMENT_PROPOSALS.md\n├── CHANGE_PLANS/\n├── CHANGE_SNAPSHOTS/\n├── FORENSIC_SNAPSHOTS/\n├── TEST_RESULTS/\n└── ROLLBACK_LOG.md\n```\n\n## Change Classification\nEvery proposed change must be classified as:\n\n### safe_auto_fix\n- Reversible configuration or documentation fixes\n- Can be applied automatically without confirmation\n- Examples: typo fixes, formatting improvements, non-critical config updates\n\n### needs_confirmation\n- Architecture or multi-skill changes\n- Requires user confirmation before execution\n- Examples: skill modifications, new scripts, dependency updates\n\n### high_risk_no_touch\n- System-level destructive changes\n- Never modify automatically\n- Examples: API key changes, credential stores, destructive operations\n\n## Protected Zones (Never Auto-Modify)\n- API keys and credential stores\n- Vector database content\n- Core system dependencies\n- Destructive file operations\n\n## Hardening Rules\n- **Maximum changes per run**: 3\n- **Maximum critical changes**: 1\n- **Targeted snapshots only**: Backup only affected files\n- **48-hour retention**: Normal snapshots cleaned after 48 hours\n- **Forensic retention**: Rollback snapshots preserved permanently\n\n## Snapshot Strategy\n- **Minimal targeted backups**: Only affected files\n- **Manifest tracking**: Metadata for rollback\n- **Rollback method**: File restoration\n- **Retention**: 48 hours normal, permanent for forensic\n\n## Validation Test Suite\n\n### Structural Tests\n- Verify critical directories exist\n- Verify skills load correctly\n- Verify imports resolve\n- Verify scripts execute\n\n### System Tests\n- Vector memory search works\n- Tavily search works\n- Firecrawl scrape works\n- Cron jobs remain registered\n\n### Ecosystem Tests\n- Error-learning-loop indexing works\n- Watchdog monitoring works\n- Janitor classification works\n- Heartbeat context load works\n\n## Incident Patterns\n- `evolution|FAILURE|test_failed`\n- `evolution|ROLLBACK|change_reverted`\n- `evolution|WARNING|dependency_drift`\n- `evolution|DETECTED|repeated_incident_pattern`\n\n## Usage\n\n### Full Evolution Cycle\n```bash\n# Run complete evolution cycle\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/system_observer.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/improvement_engine.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/change_classifier.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/change_simulator.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/snapshot_manager.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/test_runner.py\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/rollback_manager.py\n```\n\n### Targeted Improvement\n```bash\n# Apply specific improvement proposal\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/improvement_engine.py \\\n  --proposal-id \"EV-001\" \\\n  --apply\n```\n\n### System Health Check\n```bash\n# Generate system health report\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/scripts/system_observer.py \\\n  --output ~/.openclaw/workspace/system_evolution/SYSTEM_HEALTH_REPORT.md\n```\n\n## Scripts Overview\n\n### system_observer.py\n- Scans OpenClaw ecosystem using OC-Respawner registry\n- Collects system health metrics\n- Generates SYSTEM_HEALTH_REPORT.md\n\n### improvement_engine.py\n- Analyzes error-learning-loop incidents\n- Detects structural inconsistencies\n- Generates IMPROVEMENT_PROPOSALS.md\n\n### change_classifier.py\n- Classifies changes by risk level\n- Applies classification rules\n- Determines required confirmation level\n\n### change_simulator.py\n- Predicts impact of proposed changes\n- Identifies affected files and dependencies\n- Generates CHANGE_PLAN files\n\n### snapshot_manager.py\n- Creates minimal targeted backups\n- Manages snapshot manifests\n- Handles retention policies\n\n### test_runner.py\n- Executes validation test suite\n- Records test results\n- Determines pass/fail status\n\n### rollback_manager.py\n- Restores files from snapshots\n- Manages rollback operations\n- Updates ROLLBACK_LOG.md\n\n## Safety Guarantees\n1. **Non-destructive observation**: Never modify during analysis\n2. **Targeted snapshots**: Only backup affected files\n3. **Rollback guarantees**: Always able to restore previous state\n4. **Validation-first**: Test before commit\n5. **Learning integration**: All outcomes feed into error-learning-loop\n\n## Monitoring\n- **Watchdog registration**: For evolution cycles >5 minutes\n- **Progress tracking**: Step-by-step monitoring\n- **Incident reporting**: Structured incidents to error-learning-loop\n- **Outcome learning**: Feed results back into system\n\n## Performance Targets\n- **Observation time**: <30 seconds\n- **Analysis time**: <60 seconds\n- **Snapshot creation**: <10 seconds per file\n- **Test execution**: <120 seconds\n- **Rollback time**: <5 seconds per file\n\n## Security Considerations\n- **No credential access**: Never reads or modifies API keys\n- **Scope limitation**: Only modifies workspace files\n- **Confirmation required**: For needs_confirmation changes\n- **Audit trail**: All changes logged in EVOLUTION_REGISTRY.md\n\n## Maintenance\n- Update classification rules based on incidents\n- Adjust test suite as ecosystem evolves\n- Extend integration points for new skills\n- Review and clean old snapshots via workspace-janitor\n\n---\n\n**Created**: 2026‑03‑06  \n**Version**: 1.0.0  \n**Status**: Production‑Ready  \n**Integration**: Full OpenClaw ecosystem"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773104809683}}
